This paper is about image super-resolution using deep learning methods, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a lightweight network architecture, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a cascading mechanism, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
